public abstract class AbstractData<DATA extends AbstractData<?>>
extends Object

Defines common information from administration objects used to create, update and check them.

export

public ExportParser export(String... _params)
                    throws Exception
Exports this data piece from MX. The returned values from the export are checked for:
  • value is returned
  • returned export value includes exact one export for given configuration item type
  • name of the exported object is equal name
  • path of the exported object is equal ciFile()
  • file name of the export object is equal returned value from getCIFileName()

Parameters:
_params - parameters
Returns:
parsed export
Throws:
Exception - if export failed

checkSingleValue

public void checkSingleValue(ExportParser _exportParser,
                             String _kind,
                             String _tag,
                             String _value)
Checks for given _tag in the _exportParser if the _value exists and is correct defined. If _value is null, it is checked that no value is defined.

Parameters:
_exportParser - parsed export
_kind - kind of the check
_tag - tag to check
_value - value to check (or null if value is not defined)
